Lint and test discipline for this repo

Audience: internal (Junie) and contributors

1) Always run lint before committing or opening a PR
- Command: npm run lint
- Fixable issues: npm run lint:fix (then review the diff)
- The ESLint config is strict (flat config, TypeScript + React). Do not suppress rules unless discussed.

2) Run the combined check locally
- Command: npm run test:all
- This runs: lint, then the Node test suite (node --test).
- CI should mirror: npm ci && npm run test:all

3) TypeScript/React notes to avoid introducing lint errors
- No explicit any. Prefer precise types. If unavoidable, use unknown and narrow, or create a small interface/type.
- Avoid unused variables/parameters. Prefix intentional unused with _.
- Prefer function components and hooks; follow react-hooks rules (rules-of-hooks, exhaustive-deps).
- Keep ESM-only conventions (no require, no __dirname); use import.meta.*.

4) Before pushing
- npm ci (fresh) if dependencies changed
- npm run lint
- node --test (or npm run test)
- npm run build (optional smoke)

5) Quick reference
- Lint: npm run lint
- Lint (auto-fix): npm run lint:fix
- Tests: npm run test
- All: npm run test:all

Last updated: 2025-09-25